title: For Sale/Trade:  Custom Black Diamond AR
postcontent:
Up for sale or trade is a new and never fired AR-15 based on of the YHM Black Diamond Specter Carbine (http://bit.ly/15Iz8X5).  This carbine has been further improved over the YHM offering with the addition of a Rock River Arms M16 bolt carrier group, Hogue OverMolded rubber grip, and a CAA stock saddle with storage compartments.

The M16 BCG perfectly balances out the carbine gas system for optimal reliability, while the Hogue provides a comfortable interface with a consistently solid grip that performs well in all environments. The stock saddle gives an enhanced cheek weld while also providing a dual O-ring sealed storage compartment for snap-caps, spare batteries, backup bolts, or other items.  As on all Diamond carbines, the rail provides a seamless optic platform on the entire top surface and the diamond fluted barrel provides a strong, stiff, and lightweight solution that also provides superior heat dispersion when compared to standard profiled barrels.

I have some optics, ammo, and a pair of magazines that I can include for extra cash or the right trade.

These pictures show a few different optic configurations in order to provide you with a bit of inspiration for how you'd like to make this gun yours. These images show the gun with just a pair of Gen 2 MBUS sights, a 1-4x optic, and an EOTech 552 paired with a 4x flip-to-side magnifier and MBUS backups. Whether you plan on range shooting, plinking, 3-gun, or want a bit of tactical-tacticool, this AR will serve you well.  Unfortunately the EOTech and magnifier are unavailable as I am keeping these for my personal use.  It's a great gun, I am only looking to part with it because I have another AR that I built, and really do not have a plan to use this one.

Thank you for looking and if you've got any questions or want to see more specific pictures, please let me know; I have detailed knowledge and photographs.

I can negotiate on the price a bit if you want to add any more accessories. If you want a Russian SKS to throw in the safe for a collector's piece, this isn't it. If you want the best shooting SKS, then look no further. You will not find a more accurate platform for the price. The 20" barrel keeps the groups significantly tighter than my 16" Kalashnikov platforms.  The only rifle that I know which compares in this caliber is my 20" VEPR, which retails close to 800 and that's before you add another 100 for the tactical stock. Even then, this Tula can hold her own against my VEPR performance wise. Compare magazines for the SKS at under 20 dollars compared to 30-50 for the VEPR, when you can find them.
